<h1><u>News</u></h1>
<b><font size=3>August 16, 2011</font></b>: Ballroom Rush, Fall 2011<br /><br />

Before committing to a semester-long membership with the CMU Ballroom Dance Club, check out what we have to offer! Join us for our new "Ballroom Rush" event on August 29, 31, September 5, 7, from 8PM to 11PM in Rangos Ballroom, UC, and sample all the different dances we'll be teaching throughout the semester! Come with friends, as this event is FREE and open to EVERYONE in the Pittsburgh community, and enjoy performances by the competition team, sample lessons of various dances, and meeting other club members!<br /><br />

<b><font size=3>August 10, 2011</font></b>: End of Summer Semester<br /><br />
Thanks to everyone who participated in our summer lessons! We will begin our fall semester on August 29, so be on the lookout for more detailed information!<br /><br />

<b><font size=3>May 31, 2011</font></b>: Summer Lessons Start Tomorrow!<br /><br />
Our first lesson of the summer will be on Wednesday, June 1. See the calendar for times and details. Sorry for any misconceptions in the e-mails.<br /><br />

<b><font size=3>May 16, 2011</font></b>: Summer Lessons<br /><br />

Our summer lessons will begin on Wednesday, June 1. Please see the calendar for the full schedule, and fill out the JOIN! form to register (even if you were a member in the spring). Lessons will be held on Monday and Wednesday nights, and will cost $35/whole summer, $5/night, $3/lesson.<br /><br />

<b><font size=3>May 15, 2011</font></b>: Congrats, Grads!<br /><br />
We would like to congratulate all of our graduates on their successful college career! We are glad to have had each and every one of them in our club, and we hope that they enjoyed their time with us and will come back to visit! We would also like to introduce our new officers - you can see them on the "Officers" page. Please contact them if you have any questions about the club.<br /><br />

<b><font size=3>April 15, 2011</font></b>: Thank you!<br /><br />
A huge thanks to everyone who voted for us in the College Ballroom Dance Team Challenge! We came in second place, winning $5,000, and we really appreciate all the support we've received.<br /><br />
Also, stay tuned for summer lessons information!<br /><br />

<b><font size=3>March 13, 2011</font></b>: Half a semester<br /><br />
